Barcelona is a city with almost 100% of its territory consolidated, and therefore it needs to be rehabilitated and not re-built. In this context, the long-term impact is expected as a result of the following actions:
1. Improving habitability: increasing pedestrians space, creating more green areas, creating spaces for leisure and social interaction, using permeable and sustainable materials;
